1
00:00:03,040 --> 00:00:06,240
I don’t get what your problem is
that I asked Shai and the girls to sit aside for a bit.

2
00:00:06,840 --> 00:00:08,680
You don’t get that you don’t start with me when he’s around?

3
00:00:08,920 --> 00:00:10,160
I’m the problem for her.

4
00:00:10,720 --> 00:00:11,680
Ugh!

5
00:00:11,760 --> 00:00:13,920
It was only seven meters.
Come on, stop whining.

6
00:00:14,000 --> 00:00:16,239
Seven meters is fine, but why outside the umbrella?

7
00:00:17,160 --> 00:00:19,760
Why am I carrying an umbrella all day
if in the end I can’t sit in the shade?

8
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:21,760
I told you to put on sunscreen.

9
00:00:21,920 --> 00:00:24,560
Meirav, do me a favor, I’m all burnt because of you,

10
00:00:24,760 --> 00:00:25,840
so don’t start with me.

11
00:00:26,120 --> 00:00:27,040
I don’t need it anymore.

12
00:00:27,200 --> 00:00:29,000
Did you see how that guy with the paddles started with me in the end?

13
00:00:29,080 --> 00:00:30,520
Seriously, it was because you took their ball

14
00:00:30,640 --> 00:00:31,840
and didn’t want to give it back.

15
00:00:31,920 --> 00:00:34,080
He did it to me
because he was too shy to talk to me.

16
00:00:34,320 --> 00:00:36,440
He would’ve written down my number if he had a place to do it.

17
00:00:36,600 --> 00:00:38,320
He just didn’t bring his phone to the beach.
-Okay, okay,

18
00:00:38,400 --> 00:00:40,160
guys, enough, ceasefire.

19
00:00:40,240 --> 00:00:41,440
Don’t say fire, I’m burning up.

20
00:00:41,520 --> 00:00:43,640
Alright, friends, we need to focus on the mission,

21
00:00:43,720 --> 00:00:44,680
we’re getting close to the target.

22
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:46,560
House rules at the Rosen family:

23
00:00:47,360 --> 00:00:50,240
Compliment Riki a lot, finish everything on your plate,

24
00:00:50,360 --> 00:00:52,600
say everything is delicious, and most importantly, no fighting.

25
00:00:52,680 --> 00:00:53,920
I know, I know.

26
00:00:54,120 --> 00:00:55,840
I wasn’t talking to you, I was talking to Shai.

27
00:01:02,480 --> 00:01:04,920
Look at me, look at me and...

28
00:01:12,760 --> 00:01:14,880
Shabbat Shalom.
-Hello.

29
00:01:15,040 --> 00:01:16,120
I’m starving, dying here.

30
00:01:16,200 --> 00:01:19,680
Please go to the balcony,
don’t fill my house with sand.

31
00:01:19,760 --> 00:01:21,680
What, why not the shower?
-Pinchas is in there,

32
00:01:21,800 --> 00:01:25,200
he’s had enough of your visits to his shower.
-Yeah, right, right.

33
00:01:25,320 --> 00:01:28,000
Barefoot, I hope you didn’t bring tar, okay?
-No, no.

34
00:01:29,120 --> 00:01:31,760
Hi, Riki.
-Meital.

35
00:01:32,760 --> 00:01:34,560
Meirav
come here

36
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,560
I didn’t know you’d come with them from the beach.

37
00:01:37,640 --> 00:01:39,760
Why, I told you she’d come.
-No, you didn’t.

38
00:01:39,840 --> 00:01:41,760
You said
-you repressed it.

39
00:01:42,320 --> 00:01:43,680
Well, what does it matter?

40
00:01:44,080 --> 00:01:46,280
We have guests, that’s what matters.

41
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:49,520
So how are you?
-I’m good, thanks.

42
00:01:50,360 --> 00:01:53,920
Nothing new.
-It’s okay, it’ll be fine.

43
00:01:56,600 --> 00:01:59,480
Go to the balcony, I’ll bring you drinks, okay?

44
00:01:59,560 --> 00:02:01,240
Can we have some of the little schnitzels too?

45
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:04,160
You’re a schnitzel yourself, why are you so burnt?

46
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:08,080
Why did we buy you an umbrella
if you’re not using it?

47
00:02:08,600 --> 00:02:09,800
Come on, come on.
-Alright, let’s go.

48
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,120
Hello.
-Shabbat Shalom.

49
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:14,280
Shabbat Shalom.

50
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Hello.

51
00:02:16,560 --> 00:02:17,960
Hey there.
-Itamar, hi.

52
00:02:18,040 --> 00:02:21,120
What’s up? I was really worried, where have you been?

53
00:02:21,200 --> 00:02:23,120
Nowhere, why?

54
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:24,560
Riki, you know we were out this week, we just popped by...

55
00:02:24,640 --> 00:02:27,240
Sorry, wait, I have something in the kitchen right now.

56
00:02:28,840 --> 00:02:31,920
Okay, don’t make a mess for me
because Mom is coming to pick you up soon

57
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:33,960
and don’t get dirty now.

58
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:36,960
No, I’m dying, you’re really turning into your mom.

59
00:02:37,040 --> 00:02:40,560
Ouch, why insult?
-Don’t get dirty now?

60
00:02:41,120 --> 00:02:42,320
What, you think I care?

61
00:02:42,400 --> 00:02:45,680
I just can't deal with Smadar the sergeant
giving me a hard time.

62
00:02:45,760 --> 00:02:48,520
No, I knew it, I knew you don't really care
how your kids look.

63
00:02:49,560 --> 00:02:50,560
I can't believe you.

64
00:02:51,120 --> 00:02:53,760
No, I don't get it, are you mad at me
because I care or because I don't?

65
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:56,480
Because I totally don't understand where you're going with this.
Wait, wait, wait,

66
00:02:56,560 --> 00:02:58,160
Is it that time of the month
when you're...?

67
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:00,440
No, it's not, and I'm not mad
because you don't care about the kids,

68
00:03:00,520 --> 00:03:01,640
I'm mad because I care about her.

69
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:03,400
My mom?
-Your ex-wife.

70
00:03:03,480 --> 00:03:05,000
About Smadar?
-Yeah, about Smadar.

71
00:03:05,080 --> 00:03:06,760
Don't you realize how much you're investing in her?

72
00:03:07,040 --> 00:03:09,600
Dressing the kids for her,
feeding them veggies because she asked,

73
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:11,960
And don't think I didn't see
how you checked the little one's homework this week.

74
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:15,480
Tell me, what, are you normal?
Smadar asked me to keep an eye on them,

75
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,440
And besides, I didn't understand anything.

76
00:03:16,520 --> 00:03:17,960
They don't teach math normally anymore.

77
00:03:18,040 --> 00:03:19,480
You know there are no more fractions?

78
00:03:19,560 --> 00:03:20,560
Yeah, really.
There aren't.

79
00:03:20,680 --> 00:03:22,640
Don't change the subject, where was I?

80
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:25,280
So everything she asks you, you just do?

81
00:03:25,360 --> 00:03:26,520
You have no backbone at all?

82
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:29,120
What?

83
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,840
Honey, honey, enough, be reasonable.

84
00:03:32,920 --> 00:03:34,640
Smadar is the mother of my kids,

85
00:03:34,720 --> 00:03:37,200
she can't just
disappear from my life one day.

86
00:03:37,280 --> 00:03:41,000
So with all the pain, and believe me it hurts
me way more than it hurts you,

87
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:43,640
I have to do everything
my ex-wife asks me.

88
00:03:44,200 --> 00:03:47,160
Your wife?
-Former. My ex-wife.

89
00:03:48,040 --> 00:03:50,840
I have to do what she asks
because she's my ex-wife,

90
00:03:50,960 --> 00:03:53,400
because you're my future wife, for now.

91
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:55,480
I love you.

92
00:03:57,040 --> 00:03:59,360
Did you see how she looked at me? She hates me.

93
00:03:59,480 --> 00:04:00,880
Honey, come on, please,

94
00:04:01,360 --> 00:04:02,800
she doesn't hate you,

95
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:05,120
she just feels sorry for you.

96
00:04:05,680 --> 00:04:08,040
Meirav, enough, be positive, okay?

97
00:04:08,840 --> 00:04:10,960
Here, I brought you drinks,

98
00:04:11,680 --> 00:04:15,120
Pinchas finished in the shower so you can go in.

99
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:17,760
First in the shower.
-Tell me, what's wrong with you? Are you a kid?

100
00:04:17,839 --> 00:04:20,720
Shiko, let the girls go first.
-Come on, girls, let's go in,

101
00:04:21,560 --> 00:04:23,640
on tiptoes, so you don't get sand on Grandma.

102
00:04:24,680 --> 00:04:29,280
Good thing the bathtub is close,
so we don't fill your house with sand.

103
00:04:30,440 --> 00:04:31,400
Come on.

104
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:39,600
Do you think she meant our house is small?
-No, no, no,

105
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:41,760
You didn't understand her at all.

106
00:04:42,000 --> 00:04:44,040
She said that because of the...

107
00:04:44,480 --> 00:04:46,000
evil eye, that's how it is for them.

108
00:04:46,320 --> 00:04:48,240
Why didn't you tell me you were bringing her?

109
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:51,160
I would have made something special for Meirav.

110
00:04:53,440 --> 00:04:58,280
I'm going to defrost some schnitzels.
-And you didn't bring me any.

111
00:05:00,080 --> 00:05:01,400
You leave me alone like a dog.

112
00:05:02,920 --> 00:05:05,120
Do you want me to buy the necklace...

113
00:05:05,360 --> 00:05:07,480
Hey, what's up? What's going on?
-All good, everything's fine.

114
00:05:07,960 --> 00:05:09,920
The kids are dressed up.

115
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:12,160
You have good taste in dressing up, Smadar.

116
00:05:12,280 --> 00:05:14,320
Sand, sand, you're bringing in so much sand here.

117
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:17,320
Sand, shells, water, seaweed, tar, jellyfish.

118
00:05:18,840 --> 00:05:21,880
Honey, it was an accident, honey.
-I'm not mad at her.

119
00:05:21,960 --> 00:05:23,240
You're not.
-No, I'm not.

120
00:05:23,440 --> 00:05:25,680
She sees me once a year,
she can mix up my name,

121
00:05:25,840 --> 00:05:28,640
Of course, if she’s always
hearing her ex-husband’s wife’s name.

122
00:05:28,720 --> 00:05:30,160
What did I do wrong now?

123
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:33,800
Honey, Smadar is Itamar's ex-wife.

124
00:05:34,680 --> 00:05:38,080
Enough
what’s your ex-wife’s name, Oz?
_Mochal Meirav.

125
00:05:38,160 --> 00:05:40,480
Well, why should I be blamed for his serial marriages?

126
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:41,880
I see her once in a while too...

127
00:05:41,960 --> 00:05:43,920
And it’s always near their mom’s questionable food.

128
00:05:44,880 --> 00:05:46,240
I hope she doesn’t serve the...

129
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:48,160
What are those little ones called?
-Shlayklech?

130
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,640
There are knaidlach inside, right?

131
00:05:52,000 --> 00:05:54,360
Who the hell serves this horror?

132
00:05:54,600 --> 00:05:56,240
Okay, okay, relax,
I’m going to get clothes for the girls,

133
00:05:56,320 --> 00:05:58,520
Watch the girls and watch your mouth.

134
00:05:59,080 --> 00:06:01,800
I said, for crying out loud, give me a break.
-Meirav, enough.

135
00:06:14,160 --> 00:06:15,160
Well, well.

136
00:06:15,960 --> 00:06:17,560
What are you doing?
-Nothing.

137
00:06:18,600 --> 00:06:20,200
I’m looking for a comb or something,

138
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,480
I’ll comb you nicely.

139
00:06:40,440 --> 00:06:41,680
Crap.
-What happened?

140
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:43,280
Nothing happened.

141
00:06:48,760 --> 00:06:51,120
This will be our little secret.

142
00:06:52,640 --> 00:06:56,200
What’s that smell?
-Smell...

143
00:06:58,400 --> 00:06:59,280
Great.

144
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:04,360
We’ll be in the shower again soon, girls.

145
00:07:05,440 --> 00:07:09,920
I said I’m sorry
!I meant it. Talk to me already.

146
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,480
Talk to your wife.
-You’re my wife.

147
00:07:12,640 --> 00:07:13,640
Am I supposed to know that, Itamar?

148
00:07:14,200 --> 00:07:17,320
Because we hang out together every night?
Because you enjoy being with me? Because of the sex?

149
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,120
What does that have to do with anything now?

150
00:07:19,520 --> 00:07:22,040
I want to be your wife, honey,
not just the one you hang out with.

151
00:07:22,120 --> 00:07:25,040
What, you want me to suffer with you?
Because you’re on the fast track, honey.

152
00:07:25,280 --> 00:07:27,960
It’s not funny to me,
maybe being your third wife would be funny.

153
00:08:17,640 --> 00:08:22,640
You won’t believe it, Itamar and Michal
are having a crazy fight over AS-IX.

154
00:08:22,720 --> 00:08:24,200
Sex?
-What?

155
00:08:24,280 --> 00:08:26,720
Nothing, honey, nothing, it’s for adults.

156
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:29,400
What’s going on? Did something happen? There’s a bad smell here.

157
00:08:30,040 --> 00:08:31,840
Nothing, we just showered.

158
00:08:31,920 --> 00:08:34,120
What did you shower with, a branch from the Super-Pharm?

159
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:01,320
You’re not being reasonable. It slipped out,

160
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:03,440
I can’t be responsible for all my slip-ups.

161
00:09:03,520 --> 00:09:04,400
Yeah, I already know that.

162
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:07,040
Okay, enough, that’s it,
now you’ve annoyed me. Enough, stop,

163
00:09:07,120 --> 00:09:08,160
We’re done, that’s it,

164
00:09:08,240 --> 00:09:10,360
I’m really willing to go very far with you,

165
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:12,800
I’m willing to grovel,
I’m willing to tell you I love you,

166
00:09:13,000 --> 00:09:14,160
But now you’ve gone too far.

167
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:17,240
Why are you yelling like that?
-She went too far.

168
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:18,960
We have a guest here.

169
00:09:19,040 --> 00:09:21,480
Thanks, Riki, but I don’t see myself as a guest.

170
00:09:21,560 --> 00:09:23,640
I meant Meirav.

171
00:09:23,720 --> 00:09:26,040
I’m not ready for her to go to Shai’s parents.

172
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:28,000
!Say we’re yelling here.

173
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:30,080
You know how they love to talk,

174
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:32,760
they can’t keep their mouths shut.

175
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:36,640
Shabbat Shalom, I don’t have much time
because I have a date with a pair of twins.

176
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:39,920
No one wants to hear about your girls,

177
00:09:40,280 --> 00:09:42,280
we have a guest here.

178
00:09:42,920 --> 00:09:44,120
Worth it?
-Meirav.

179
00:09:45,920 --> 00:09:47,160
Shabbat Shalom and see you later.
-Adam.

180
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,560
How’s it going?
-Hey there.

181
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:52,200
We just got back from the beach.
-Hey, Meirav.

182
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:53,720
What...

183
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:57,640
How are you?
-Great, thanks.

184
00:09:58,120 --> 00:09:59,840
So, can you tell I got some sun?

185
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,600
What are you doing here?

186
00:10:02,920 --> 00:10:04,600
The sun keeps moving on me.

187
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:09,320
Thanks, thanks.

188
00:10:10,760 --> 00:10:13,280
I'm starving, this is really making me hungry.

189
00:10:13,360 --> 00:10:15,400
Flipping over?
-No,

190
00:10:16,000 --> 00:10:17,840
The smell of my skin is making me crave shawarma.

191
00:10:18,400 --> 00:10:19,720
I'm dying of heat here.

192
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:22,560
Are they done in the shower?
-Shani's still in there.

193
00:10:22,680 --> 00:10:25,000
I'm in trouble because at this rate, the sun's moving!

194
00:10:25,600 --> 00:10:26,680
I'll be here until noon, no doubt.

195
00:10:27,240 --> 00:10:28,880
Enjoy!
-Thanks.

196
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:32,440
Is this still taken?
-It's coming, it's coming.

197
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:36,520
Have you seen my aftershave?
-No.

198
00:10:38,120 --> 00:10:38,960
It's not here.

199
00:10:40,800 --> 00:10:43,000
I don't get why she buys
that air freshener,

200
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,760
it stinks. Do me a favor, sit down,

201
00:10:44,880 --> 00:10:47,520
no matter what you did, don’t use it next time.

202
00:10:47,960 --> 00:10:49,480
It’s not me, Pinchas.

203
00:10:56,440 --> 00:10:58,000
You won’t believe the scene I had at the beach.

204
00:10:58,400 --> 00:10:59,760
I just had a Diet Coke,

205
00:10:59,920 --> 00:11:01,880
you know, it has
the worst burps,

206
00:11:01,960 --> 00:11:03,680
maybe except for dark beer.

207
00:11:04,000 --> 00:11:05,880
Hey, also dark soda.

208
00:11:06,280 --> 00:11:08,640
Do you think dark drinks
make more burps?

209
00:11:08,880 --> 00:11:10,640
So, who took my aftershave?

210
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:16,040
Adam?
-What?

211
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:19,560
Oh, come on, why would I use
your garbage juice? I just got here.

212
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:30,120
What are you playing?

213
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:34,280
What are you playing?

214
00:11:35,760 --> 00:11:37,520
What are you playing?

215
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,040
Am I breaking the record?
-What?

216
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,680
He’s breaking his own record.

217
00:11:42,840 --> 00:11:46,560
Oh, nice, show me for a sec.
-Why?

218
00:11:47,080 --> 00:11:49,960
Good thing you came, I was about to be roasted.

219
00:11:50,040 --> 00:11:51,560
Yeah, honestly, you really look ready.

220
00:11:52,560 --> 00:11:53,760
How's your sister?
-You wouldn’t believe it.

221
00:11:53,840 --> 00:11:55,400
So far, she’s managed to insult your mom,

222
00:11:55,600 --> 00:11:58,960
call Michal Smadar,
ruin Raz's record in the game,

223
00:11:59,040 --> 00:12:00,680
not counting the accumulated calls to Adam.

224
00:12:00,760 --> 00:12:02,880
So we’re optimistic.
-And cautious.

225
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:05,360
It was a really good idea to bring her.
-Thanks.

226
00:12:05,520 --> 00:12:06,440
Alright, go. Go take a shower.

227
00:12:15,280 --> 00:12:16,680
Why?

228
00:12:20,160 --> 00:12:21,840
Do you need help with something?

229
00:12:21,920 --> 00:12:25,200
No, no, no, everything's great, all set here.

230
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:27,320
We're glad you came

231
00:12:27,960 --> 00:12:31,400
with short notice or no notice at all.

232
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:35,280
You know, you don’t have to go out of your way for me.

233
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:38,640
What do you mean because of you and what do you mean go out of my way?

234
00:12:38,920 --> 00:12:40,960
Excuse me, I’ll be right back.

235
00:12:41,920 --> 00:12:43,640
I’ll keep an eye on the tsimmes.

236
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,320
Oh no,

237
00:12:50,760 --> 00:12:52,000
Shloimel.

238
00:12:59,360 --> 00:13:00,480
Hey, sweetie.

239
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:05,640
Of course, I hate that this happens.

240
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:10,240
How about you help Grandma Riki with the food?
-What?

241
00:13:10,760 --> 00:13:11,920
Oh, did you get that?

242
00:13:12,000 --> 00:13:13,560
We can make a salad.

243
00:13:14,120 --> 00:13:16,040
Here, this is your knife.

244
00:13:16,880 --> 00:13:19,760
Your whole family is so careful and considerate with her.

245
00:13:20,120 --> 00:13:21,640
Why again?

246
00:13:21,840 --> 00:13:23,920
She's actually a really nice girl inside.

247
00:13:24,120 --> 00:13:26,000
Dad, do me a favor, don’t get involved, okay?

248
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:27,720
What’s so nice about her?

249
00:13:27,800 --> 00:13:31,360
She kind of scares me.
-Scares you?

250
00:13:31,560 --> 00:13:33,480
No, of course not, but...

251
00:13:33,840 --> 00:13:35,360
I mean a little.

252
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:39,640
I'm afraid she'll go tell her mom everything.

253
00:13:40,040 --> 00:13:41,840
What?
-What about her mom now?

254
00:13:41,920 --> 00:13:43,480
What about her mom now, huh?

255
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:47,320
Don’t you remember what happened on Rosh Hashanah?
-Where were you on Rosh Hashanah?

256
00:13:47,400 --> 00:13:50,880
Wait, wait, wait, who are you talking about?
-About Meirav, the one here.

257
00:13:51,120 --> 00:13:52,640
We were talking about Smadar.
-Smadar.

258
00:13:53,040 --> 00:13:54,080
Oh, Smadar,

259
00:13:55,200 --> 00:13:58,960
it would have been so much easier
if she brought her sister.

260
00:13:59,040 --> 00:13:59,880
See?

261
00:13:59,960 --> 00:14:01,480
You see? It’s already passed.

262
00:14:01,560 --> 00:14:06,160
And we don’t need to tell anyone about it ever, okay?

263
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:11,080
What’s with Meirav, what happened to her?

264
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:13,680
The girl? She got cut a little.

265
00:14:14,840 --> 00:14:16,400
What do you mean she got cut? Did you give her a knife?

266
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,880
She’s too little.
-Okay, come on, how was I supposed to know?

267
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:20,920
Besides, don’t worry,
it’s fine, I talked to her about it.

268
00:14:21,480 --> 00:14:22,360
What do you mean you talked to her?

269
00:14:22,960 --> 00:14:25,960
She won’t tell, we said it’s our little secret.

270
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:28,800
Secret? Did you even explain to her what a secret is?

271
00:14:29,360 --> 00:14:31,760
Didn’t I do well?
-No, Meirav, no. She’s a little girl.

272
00:14:32,120 --> 00:14:34,840
Little kids, when something happens to them
they need to tell their parents.

273
00:14:34,920 --> 00:14:38,680
And not keep secrets with strange adults.
-I didn’t think about that.

274
00:14:38,760 --> 00:14:39,760
Oh, great.

275
00:14:40,800 --> 00:14:41,800
I’ll go talk to Itamar about this.

276
00:14:42,360 --> 00:14:43,920
No, no, no, I already messed up with his wife earlier,

277
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:45,240
let me handle this,

278
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:48,240
I’ll explain to the girl that I was wrong.
You’ll see, everything will be fine,

279
00:14:48,320 --> 00:14:50,560
it’ll be our little secret.

280
00:14:51,760 --> 00:14:52,600
Okay.

281
00:15:13,520 --> 00:15:15,320
What was that?
-I don’t know.

282
00:15:15,800 --> 00:15:17,440
I’m in the middle of something.
-No, Dad...

283
00:15:18,440 --> 00:15:20,960
Shai, seriously, you broke my aftershave.

284
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:22,560
I didn’t mean to, it was already broken.

285
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:23,520
What are you, a kid?

286
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:25,600
I heard you behind the door breaking it.

287
00:15:25,680 --> 00:15:26,680
But Dad, what are you...

288
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:29,400
Riki.
-Come on, close the door, Dad.

289
00:15:32,560 --> 00:15:33,680
Sit.

290
00:15:33,760 --> 00:15:38,360
By the way, I talked to Smadar this week.
-No, I’m dying.

291
00:15:39,920 --> 00:15:43,120
Enough, Mom, you’re killing me,
we’re divorced, that’s enough already.

292
00:15:43,680 --> 00:15:44,840
Of course.

293
00:15:45,120 --> 00:15:47,840
She said you’re a good dad.
-Very nice.

294
00:15:48,840 --> 00:15:51,200
Why are you following her? Let her be alone for a bit.

295
00:15:51,280 --> 00:15:53,400
No, I don’t think so.
-You, don’t get involved.

296
00:15:53,480 --> 00:15:54,440
Sorry.

297
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:57,520
So, are we eating today too?
-Excuse me for a moment.

298
00:15:57,640 --> 00:16:01,000
If you had acted like that with Smadar,
maybe you wouldn’t have separated.

299
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,600
I found it.
-What?

300
00:16:02,680 --> 00:16:03,920
The aftershave.
-Too bad.

301
00:16:04,120 --> 00:16:05,760
Oh no.
- Shai broke it for me.

302
00:16:05,840 --> 00:16:08,040
What?
- Yeah, broke it, broke it.

303
00:16:08,120 --> 00:16:09,720
Did he know it was the last one?

304
00:16:09,840 --> 00:16:11,360
Okay, fine, Riki,
no need to dance on his conscience.

305
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:13,360
I’ll buy you a new one, okay?

306
00:16:13,440 --> 00:16:14,720
But it’s not possible,

307
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:19,680
the company that made those aftershaves
went bankrupt five weeks ago.

308
00:16:19,840 --> 00:16:23,680
No big deal, just get a new one,
I love new scents too,

309
00:16:23,760 --> 00:16:26,800
I put it on myself
and imagine I’m someone else.

310
00:16:28,880 --> 00:16:31,960
Bonjour, it’s from Apple Breeze.

311
00:16:32,640 --> 00:16:36,360
Pinchas is a bit more conservative.
- Okay, it’s just a scent

312
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,400
and to be honest, it wasn’t that great.

313
00:16:38,520 --> 00:16:41,200
Meirav, are you crazy?
That’s been his scent since they met.

314
00:16:41,280 --> 00:16:42,160
Now you’re stepping into a minefield.

315
00:16:42,240 --> 00:16:47,080
Riki, what Meirav meant, basically,
is to just soften the blow, yeah,

316
00:16:47,160 --> 00:16:48,680
so it’s not that bad it happened,

317
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:52,280
not that it stinks or anything! Like, right?
- Of course.

318
00:16:52,360 --> 00:16:55,280
Didn’t you say you wanted
to tell a story to the kids on the balcony?

319
00:16:55,360 --> 00:16:56,280
Yeah.

320
00:16:56,880 --> 00:17:00,400
Kids, come to the balcony, I have a surprise.

321
00:17:05,319 --> 00:17:06,800
But why is it like this? You didn’t get divorced?

322
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:09,280
Of course, babe, I divorced her,

323
00:17:09,400 --> 00:17:10,599
but my mom hasn’t yet.

324
00:17:10,680 --> 00:17:12,119
Why aren’t you doing something?

325
00:17:12,200 --> 00:17:14,920
What do you want me to do?
Get divorced from my mom?

326
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,560
Not talk to my mom anymore?
- No, but...

327
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:22,680
So to reduce the friction
I do everything Smadar asks me to,

328
00:17:22,760 --> 00:17:27,200
discipline, cleanliness, order. Just to avoid
her calling my mom

329
00:17:27,280 --> 00:17:29,520
and then you get more trouble from her.

330
00:17:29,600 --> 00:17:31,720
So all this because you’re struggling

331
00:17:31,800 --> 00:17:33,920
with your mom’s nonsense?
- No, but...

332
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:39,120
So my mom just brings up
Smadar’s name again,

333
00:17:39,200 --> 00:17:41,400
you see how she treats her,

334
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:43,680
and then you get annoyed.
- Yeah, but...

335
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:46,360
And I don’t want you to get hurt by all this nonsense

336
00:17:46,440 --> 00:17:48,440
that has nothing to do with you, babe.

337
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:52,120
What, so all this is my fault?
- Not because of you, babe,

338
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:55,480
for you.
- For me?

339
00:17:55,560 --> 00:17:56,800
Of course, babe.

340
00:17:56,880 --> 00:17:59,120
So basically, it’s for you that you’re hysterical

341
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:01,720
that the kids won’t get dirty?
- Of course, babe,

342
00:18:01,800 --> 00:18:05,480
it’s all for you, I love you.

343
00:18:05,960 --> 00:18:08,560
Babe.
- Let it be quiet

344
00:18:10,120 --> 00:18:12,240
Babe
Babe

345
00:18:12,800 --> 00:18:15,000
This chocolate is not a secret,

346
00:18:15,080 --> 00:18:18,360
and if you want, you can
tell your parents everything,

347
00:18:18,440 --> 00:18:20,680
and there are no secrets between us, okay?

348
00:18:20,760 --> 00:18:21,840
Okay.
- Okay.

349
00:18:21,920 --> 00:18:23,000
More.

350
00:18:23,920 --> 00:18:25,120
Let’s see what I have left.

351
00:18:27,640 --> 00:18:29,240
Here.
- Thanks.

352
00:18:30,880 --> 00:18:32,200
And I just want to remind you

353
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:35,240
that if you want candies and surprises from me

354
00:18:35,320 --> 00:18:37,240
next time we meet,

355
00:18:37,320 --> 00:18:40,000
then it’s better not to tell your parents what happened.

356
00:18:40,440 --> 00:18:41,600
But you don’t have to,

357
00:18:41,720 --> 00:18:44,880
you can choose to tell and not get chocolate

358
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,280
or not tell and get it.

359
00:18:48,800 --> 00:18:51,480
Wait, wasn’t that you?
- No, it wasn’t me, I swear,

360
00:18:51,560 --> 00:18:52,640
it was rolled in a towel.

361
00:18:55,720 --> 00:18:56,800
Meirav.

362
00:18:56,880 --> 00:18:57,880
K'
Meiravi
Beni

363
00:18:57,960 --> 00:18:59,400
That's why it smelled like air freshener.

364
00:18:59,960 --> 00:19:02,480
She's good.
-Oh my God.

365
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:06,320
Say, do you think we can...
-A little longer, just a bit more.

366
00:19:07,600 --> 00:19:09,200
Well, at least nothing happened to me.
-Yeah.

367
00:19:12,080 --> 00:19:13,000
The shleikelar?

368
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:14,240
Of course.
-Great.

369
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:17,040
I know exactly what to do
so she won't want to come here anymore.

370
00:19:17,120 --> 00:19:18,120
Thanks.

371
00:19:18,200 --> 00:19:21,640
Smadar loved my shleikelar so much.

372
00:19:21,720 --> 00:19:24,960
No, I'm dying.
-Forget it, babe, half an hour and it's over.

373
00:19:25,280 --> 00:19:26,280
Aya.

374
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:30,840
Did you cut yourself on the glass?
-Yeah, but not deep because it went through the flip-flop.

375
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:34,200
You need to disinfect it with alcohol.
-No, it's already sanitized.

376
00:19:34,280 --> 00:19:37,000
That was my last bottle.
-Dad, it's not me,

377
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:37,920
It's from...
-Enough, Shai.

378
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,920
I'll check online where to get one of those.

379
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,000
What is it?

380
00:19:43,560 --> 00:19:46,920
Why are they... no way.
-What happened?

381
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:48,240
Why are they so dirty?

382
00:19:48,800 --> 00:19:51,760
Nonsense, it's chocolate,
it washes out, I know about this.

383
00:19:52,320 --> 00:19:54,360
You know about laundry?
-What?

384
00:19:54,600 --> 00:19:56,040
I know about chocolate.

385
00:19:56,120 --> 00:19:57,280
I can't believe this...

386
00:19:57,360 --> 00:20:00,280
Thank you so much really.
What do I say to Smadar now?

387
00:20:00,360 --> 00:20:03,000
Smadar?
-No, no, no, no.

388
00:20:03,080 --> 00:20:06,480
I liked calling her Smadar-malda.
-Smadar?

389
00:20:06,560 --> 00:20:07,960
Now.
-Not yet.

390
00:20:08,720 --> 00:20:11,080
Are we eating today too?
-Yeah, come on.

391
00:20:15,400 --> 00:20:18,640
I really love all these stews.

392
00:20:19,200 --> 00:20:22,520
I defrosted a shleikelar for you-
-Yeah, I know.

393
00:20:23,120 --> 00:20:27,680
Do you already smell it?
-Yeah. I peeked in the kitchen

394
00:20:27,760 --> 00:20:30,800
and saw them in the pot, but you forgot to add spices.

395
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:32,920
-Just a bit.

396
00:20:33,480 --> 00:20:35,000
Now?
-Not yet.

397
00:20:35,720 --> 00:20:37,520
Bode?
R, do you have
what is it, coach, Mo

398
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:40,800
Meirav.
-She's in the cut.

399
00:20:40,880 --> 00:20:41,880
What in...

400
00:20:43,720 --> 00:20:44,880
What do I say to Smadar now?

401
00:20:44,960 --> 00:20:46,280
No, that's what you have to say

402
00:20:46,360 --> 00:20:47,840
instead of asking your daughter if she's okay?

403
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:49,240
If I ask, what will she answer me?

404
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:52,680
...iPhone?

405
00:20:52,760 --> 00:20:54,200
Okay. Sweetie, are you okay?

406
00:20:57,920 --> 00:20:59,720
I told you.
-What did she say?

407
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:02,560
That her stomach hurts,
she wants to call mom on the iPhone.

408
00:21:02,880 --> 00:21:04,080
What stomach?

409
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:08,000
Tell me, are you normal?
Did you cut her in the stomach too?

410
00:21:08,080 --> 00:21:10,640
No, of course not, I just gave her a little chocolate.

411
00:21:10,720 --> 00:21:12,760
With milk?
-I think so.

412
00:21:12,840 --> 00:21:13,680
Not good.

413
00:21:13,760 --> 00:21:15,560
Now?
-Not yet.

414
00:21:15,760 --> 00:21:17,000
Here’s the shleikelar.

415
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:18,880
Be careful, it's hot.

416
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:26,200
What happened to the shleikelar?
-It's mujaddara.

417
00:21:26,760 --> 00:21:27,760
Watch out, she's throwing up.

418
00:21:28,320 --> 00:21:29,240
Now.

419
00:21:29,320 --> 00:21:32,200
On this occasion, I want to say
that I don't think I'll be here next week,

420
00:21:32,280 --> 00:21:33,440
we're going on vacation.

421
00:21:36,600 --> 00:21:39,120
Do you think your parents noticed
that you said you’re going?

422
00:21:39,200 --> 00:21:40,040
Because it was a total mess there.

423
00:21:40,120 --> 00:21:41,280
Yeah, we’re counting on it.

424
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,680
What do you mean?
-No, nothing.

425
00:21:44,240 --> 00:21:45,560
You really didn’t tell them I’m coming.

426
00:21:45,640 --> 00:21:47,880
Of course, and we purposely went to the beach first.

427
00:21:48,200 --> 00:21:52,440
Oh, it was a little trick, good job.

428
00:21:53,040 --> 00:21:53,920
No...

429
00:21:54,560 --> 00:21:56,200
Wait, so basically you’re using me.

430
00:21:56,280 --> 00:21:57,720
What? No way, who’s using you?

431
00:21:57,800 --> 00:21:59,520
You owe me
-What?

432
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:00,800
How much?
-More.

433
00:22:01,160 --> 00:22:02,040
To...

434
00:22:02,320 --> 00:22:03,760
Fine, okay, more.
-Alright.

435
00:22:14,320 --> 00:22:16,600
You need to, you need to look at him completely.

436
00:22:16,680 --> 00:22:18,480
There are crackers inside, right?

437
00:22:18,880 --> 00:22:21,560
It’s here
-without here

438
00:22:24,040 --> 00:22:27,480
No, she didn’t say here
-let’s go back to the beginning of the sentence.

439
00:22:28,360 --> 00:22:29,480
No, I’m dying.

440
00:22:43,320 --> 00:22:47,280
Here are the sliders. Be careful, they’re hot.

441
00:22:48,200 --> 00:22:49,520
Sorry, sorry.

442
00:22:50,840 --> 00:22:52,080
The sliders.

443
00:22:52,680 --> 00:22:56,000
You’re killing me inside, Sabrine.

